cron and crontab 

# cron -> daemon (background processes) to execute scheduled commands
# crontab -> maintain crontab files
# with crontab -l you can display the current crontab.
# crontab -e -> Edit the current crontab.
# inside vim, give the wished time when the comman should be executet,
# minutes hour * * * for day month year
# write the command after the date /bin/sh /media/abc.sh
# create a abc.sh file in the media folder with a script: touch /media/file.txt
